4771580209", "url": "https://x.com/nakul/status/2049880224771580209", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/nakul/status/2049880224771580209", "text": "Why experts never start companies. Why averages don't apply to individuals. Why he spent 80% of the first year recruiting.\n\nBipul Sinha (@bipulsinha), Founder and CEO of @RubrikInc.\n\nImmigrant. VC. Founder. Philosopher.\n\nNew episode of @KnuckleUpHQ is live \u2193\n--\n\n00:00 Intro\n\n01:47 State of intellect vs state of will\n\n03:09 Bipul\u2019s maniacal recruiting philosophy\n\n07:06 Recruiting is like starting a religion\n\n11:44 Will vs skill: you can teach one but not the other\n\n14:28 Adhog\u0101m\u012b: fighting mental downward slopes\n\n16:03 Why Bipul thinks product market fit is dead\n\n19:25 Nobody knows anything (and what that means for you)\n\n23:06 Three questions that launched Rubrik\u2019s AI transformation\n\n32:04 \u201cEither you go AI or you die\u201d\n\n33:42 There is only one moat\n\n35:15 When Rubrik\u2019s growth collapsed overnight\n\n41:28 \u201cMaximal Thinking\u201d: How to succeed amidst uncertainty\n\n45:12 Quickfire round: red flags, worst VC advice, more\n\n47:29 Bipul\u2019s advice to his 25-year-old self", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 44, "replyCount": 4, "likeCount": 581, "quoteCount": 4, "viewCount": 1037080, "createdAt": "Thu Apr 30 15:55:05 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 283, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049880224771580209", "displayTextRange": [0, 274], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "nakul", "url": "https://x.com/nakul", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/nakul", "id": "221546840", "name": "Nakul Mandan", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1263644697865580544/OQqSrzy5_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/221546840/1398236509", "descript